<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Natural fires related to lightning strikes are relatively uncommon because of insufficient fuels. Stand cover is generally lower than with related <i>Artemisia tridentata </i>types. The presence of invasive, non-native grasses may increase the frequency of fires. <i>Ephedra viridis </i>sprouts vigorously and seedlings establish following fire (Anderson 2001e), but Conrad (1987) reports that plants do not sprout after chaparral fires.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
